What are your 2023 resolutions? Or even your word for this year? My New Year’s Resolution: Not entertaining people that don’t meet my standards of a good friend / partner. I think my default setting is to see the good in everyone and ignore red flags. My default is that if you only love me at 50% it’s okay, I’ll just love you at 150%. Instead of seeing an unhealed person or someone doesn’t treat me well, I see someone who needs care—someone who has become this way because of the world around them. Someone with a story that if I just understand, I can help. BUT IT’S NOT YOUR MF PROBLEM 🚨🚨🚨It’s not a bad thing to feel a calling to understand and heal those around you, but that energy has to be used so selectively. And so my theme of the year is to raise those standards. Everything in life is an exchange of energy. Your energy, your time is your most valuable currency. Spend wisely on those who are reciprocating and investing back in you 🤍 And if someone isn’t meeting those standards, give yourself permission to let them go 🤝🏾

POV: HAPPY SEERAT!!! My irl friends always make fun of me that I do the “Seerat face” on IG when 99% of the time—this photo dump is what I really look like 😂 

All these pics are from the last 6ish months— and I think one of the biggest lessons I’ve learned in this time is that happiness is a state of mind and it comes from within. It starts in the morning with saying out loud what you’re grateful for, and it ends with thanking the universe that you get to be here another day. I think I’m happiest when I’m traveling, surrounded by people who genuinely love me and see my light (and visa versa) ✨ I think it’s also important to remember that you don’t need to *earn* joy—it’s not something that you indulge in once you hit a certain metric at work or once you achieve a life milestone. It’s something you deserve everyday 💖 (last 6 months have also had the lowest lows—but just not ready to talk about it yet) I think the lows have actually helped me internally reframe what happiness is to me 🦋

ALSO how many sparklers are in this dump 😂 Like crows to aluminum, like moths to a flame, there must be a scientific reason why we’re obsessed with sparklers 😂🪄✨
.

I feel like it’s EQUALLY important to talk about the hair growth products that didn’t work for me specifically! BUT they may have worked for you! What’s worked / not worked for your hair growth? ⬇️

1. I bought this iRestore Laser Hair Growth System in 2021 and used it as directed for 8 months and I can’t say it made any difference in my hair growth! I’ve seen amazing before and afters on their site but for me—it just didn’t do anything for me 🥲 And for $600 I was pretty bummed out lol 

2. The ordinary serum for hair density I also purchased myself and I can’t say it did much. Caffeine is an ingredient that works really well for my hair growth but I do coffee rinses / coffee scrubs in the shower anyway and I feel like that’s more effective than this particular serum! It also made my hair a little greasy with each daily application (Vegamour and Philip Kingsley don’t make my hair greasy) so I didn’t feel like I could use daily 😅

3. “Hair Growth” shampoos or conditioners are simply not on your scalp long enough to make a difference in stimulating your scalp. There’s no shampoo that’s clinically proven to support hair regrowth. BUT the right shampoo / conditioner for your hair needs, type, porosity ect can be part of a routine to keep your hair healthy! But it’s not going to actually make your hair grow 👀
.
.
.
.

SAVE FOR YOUR NEXT SHOWER & FOLLOW FOR MORE!! (Amazon link for the silicone massager mold is in my bio!) I lost about half my hair in 2019 and made it my mission to grow it back! 😅 I’m hoping this helps anyone struggling to keep their hair from falling out ❤️ Feel free to send it to anyone you think it may help! I’ve been using rosemary & mint hair rinses the last 2 years and it’s made a BIG difference 🤌🏾

Trying this new frozen technique thanks to @afsennah!! She makes amazing hair growth videos! 🫶🏾 

Rosemary hair rinses are an amazing way to grow your hair fast! The secret ingredient in rosemary is ursolic acid: an  anti-inflammatory antioxidant that can help calm an inflamed scalp while bringing more oxygen and nutrients to the hair follicles. 🙌🏾 It basically creates an ideal environment for hair to grow faster, or for new hair to start growing again. 🥰 I’ve been adding mint because mint has a high amount of anti-bacterial and antifungal properties along with being one of the highest sources of carotene and antioxidants! 

I do this once a week after shampoo-ing and conditioning my hair & I DON’T rinse it out! 🥰 As with any DIY, it takes consistency to see a difference! Let me know if you guys have any questions!! 💜

Wellness is for absolutely EVERYONE! I’m so happy to see things like haldi doodh, hair oiling, yoga ect help people live their best lives! The knowledge is absolutely not meant to be gate kept, but rather shared with people of all ethnicities!

But you can’t extract what you want from a culture without crediting or respecting the culture. Or at the very least, buying from South Asian owned brands to support the community these practices originate from. I see so many “trends” on tiktok like hair slugging, golden lattes, turmeric masks, oil pulling, ghee ect, without any credit as to where it comes from. When someone with lighter skin does it—it’s trendy. When we do it, we’re made fun of.

The worst feeling is when the people who use these practices don’t have respect for the culture or worse, profit off of South Asian wellness practices by “going to India and discovering wellness”...only to bottle and sell it at 100 times the cost. It feels like people want the wellness knowledge of India—just minus the Indians. 

Just some Monday night thoughts—what do you think?

SAVE FOR THIS WEEKEND—I promise it’s actually so so simple! LOVED Emma’s look from the Met Gala and wanted to create my own version that suited my brown eyes and almond shape! 🦋💙 I use the liquid from 2 different shades of blue to add color to the inner and outer thirds of the eye! Then in the negative space in between, I smudge the whole eye to bring some of the blue onto the lid and create a controlled mess! Top it off with some glitter and finish off with a heavy black pencil liner in the waterline! I also smudged it out with the same blue to tie the look together 🥰💙 SO HARD FOR ME to not add any top eyeliner or false lashes but I love how this look turned out!

I am NOT a doctor and I just want to talk about my journey but please consult a doctor if you’re experiencing balding / hair loss.

A happy little Seelu! 🐘 Here are life lessons I wanted to share as I turn one year older! If we are all part of the same divine light, every person you encounter is you—from a different timeline, dimension, frequency, and elevation. If all time is happening at the same time, (on a plane rather than linear), each new person you meet is you meeting you in real time. So lead with the same kindness you would want to be shown…because that literally is you. 

The universe has your back—and she has had your back from the second you were born. Divine timing is too beautiful and complex for us to understand—so all we can do is trust her.

You create the reality around you. There is no version of the past, present, or future that isn’t from the POV of a person. A person with bias. So as we all experience our version of reality—or rather consciously interpret our version of reality, we might as well be delusional. When I believe something is going to happen for me, I speak in the present progressive tense as though it’s already happening. It’s inevitable. The universe is conspiring to make it happen for me. Believe that you are the universe’s golden child. 

What you believe about yourself is the only opinion that matters. The truth is—only you know your intentions and heart. What people say is 99% a reflection of them. When they send hate your way, it’s because they don’t love themselves. When they shame you for what you do, it’s because they or family members would shame them for the same actions. Once you realize all the other sims characters in this video game are projecting onto you—you can free yourself from the burden of their opinions.

Listen to how you feel after hanging out with friends. Your gut will always tell you the truth. I’ve had gut feelings about people for years that I wish I didn’t ignore. And if all time is happening at the same time: perhaps gut feelings are a form of time travel. Something to your “present self” from your “future self”. A warning to give your light and time to a relationship that’s worth cultivating—where you’re receiving the same love and energy you give.
